The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, Feb. 22: The Reserve Bank of India has asked the states to start fiscal correction at the earliest, to arrest the deteriorating fiscal position. In a study on state finances 2009-10, the RBI said the gross fiscal deficit of most states had risen in the backdrop of the financial crisis and revenue account of 23 states were likely to be adversely impacted.                            
	 Mumbai, Feb. 22: The Airports Authority of India has rejected Kingfisher Airlines request to lower interest rate on dues amounting to Rs 140 crore, AAI chairman V.P. Agarwal said. The dues are for a period of up to January, he said.                            
	 Mumbai, Feb. 22: Banco Products (India) will acquire the Netherlands-based Nederlandse Radiateuren Fabroiek BV and its subsidiaries for 17.70 million euros (about Rs 106 crore).                             
	 New Delhi, Feb. 22: The government has operationalised eight dispute resolution panels of the income tax department to resolve disputes between the department and taxpayers, including settling issues of foreign firms operating in India.                             
	 New Delhi, Feb. 22: Prabeer Kumar Basu was today promoted and appointed as the new agriculture secretary.
                                                                                                                          
